Completed slice:
- 2026-05-13: Completed TypeScript tree-shaking message filtering, switchable facade evidence, SvelteKit provider example, `linguini test-data`, and CLDR generated-range clippy cleanup.

Implementation decisions:
- TypeScript target config now accepts `tree_shaking = true` and `messages = [...]`; `messages` without tree-shaking is rejected.
- Tree-shaking filtering is explicit and deterministic: only selected message ids or selected group prefixes are emitted in locale modules and `.d.ts` files.
- Generated TypeScript facade remains `createLinguini`/`configureLinguini`; `configureLinguini` accepts a language getter so one app-level source variable can switch `lgl.*(...)` output.
- `linguini test-data` emits JSON rendered samples for each configured locale, schema enum variants, grouped messages, and representative numeric plural values.
- Test-data rendering is split under `crates/linguini-cli/src/project/test_data/` to keep CLI files below the size gate.
- CLDR build-time plural Rust generation emits `RangeInclusive::contains` for generated range checks instead of requiring a clippy allow in `compiled.rs`.
- `cargo fmt --all` normalized existing unformatted Rust files across the workspace.
- Syntax tests were split into `crates/linguini-syntax/src/tests/` modules. Near-limit source files remain split-required before future growth: `crates/linguini-syntax/src/lexer.rs`, `crates/linguini-syntax/src/parser/locale_parser.rs`, `crates/linguini-analyzer/src/lib.rs`, and `crates/linguini-cldr/build/plural_rule.rs`.

